  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and saute until translucent.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the scotch bonnet pepper, thyme, allspice, salt, and black pepper, and stir well.",
    "Add the soaked and drained navy beans, and stir to combine.",
    "Add 4 cups of water to the pot, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low, and simmer for 45 minutes, or until the beans are tender.",
    "Stir in the lacquer-glaze, and cook for an additional 10 minutes.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs, if desired."
